HEADWORD: Popliteal
<hw>Pop*lit"e*al</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>poples</ets>, <ets>-itis</ets>, the ham.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the ham; in the region of the ham, or behind
the knee joint; <as>as, the <ex>popliteal</ex> space</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poplitic</ent>⟦br⟧
